1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,491
Remember, it pays in every way to think big.

2
00:00:05,840 --> 00:00:07,730
Don't sell yourself short.

3
00:00:07,920 --> 00:00:10,531
Conquer the crime of self-deprecation.

4
00:00:10,721 --> 00:00:12,690
Concentrate on your assets.

5
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:15,011
You're better than you think you are.

6
00:00:15,011 --> 00:00:16,451
2.

7
00:00:16,801 --> 00:00:19,411
Use the big thinkers vocabulary.

8
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:22,210
Use big, bright, cheerful words.

9
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:26,931
Use words that promise victory, hope, happiness, pleasure.

10
00:00:27,201 --> 00:00:32,771
Avoid words that create unpleasant images of failure, defeat, grief.

11
00:00:32,771 --> 00:00:34,371
3.

12
00:00:34,721 --> 00:00:36,291
Stretch your vision.

13
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:39,331
See what can be, not just what is.

14
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:44,451
Practice adding value to things, to people, and to yourself.

15
00:00:44,451 --> 00:00:46,051
4.

16
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:48,690
Get the big view of your job.

17
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:52,690
Think, really think your present job is important.

18
00:00:52,960 --> 00:00:58,610
That next promotion depends mostly on how you think toward your present job.

19
00:00:58,610 --> 00:01:00,291
5.

20
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:02,851
Think above trivial things.

21
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:05,650
Focus your attention on big objectives.

22
00:01:05,761 --> 00:01:11,650
Before getting involved in a petty matter, ask yourself, is it really important?

23
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:15,331
Grow big by thinking big.

